  "prompt": "What does add on item on Amazon mean?",
  "response": "An \"Add-on Item\" on Amazon refers to products that are available for purchase only when your order meets a minimum requirement for total value. This means that you cannot buy these items individually; they must be included in an order that reaches a specified amount (usually around $25). \n\nThe purpose of Add-on Items is to encourage customers to purchase more products at once, making it more cost-effective for Amazon to fulfill smaller orders. Typically, these items are lower-cost goods like small household items, accessories, or other low-ticket products. When browsing, you'll see which items are categorized as Add-on Items, and they will only be available for purchase if your cart's total meets the required threshold.",
